description:
Three things set Yank Sing apart from many competitors in SF:

1) Really attentive, excellent service (no joke!);
2) Many creative seafood dumpling options that you can't find elsewhere;
3) The price - you'll pay at least 2X more here so (1) and (2) better be worth it to you!

All joking aside, this is one of the best dim sum experiences in SF if you can tolerate the very, very long waits and horrible parking options (Rincon center). They have an amazing selection of teas (but they're also quite pricey) and have the best house-made chili/XO sauce on this planet.

If you want to experience the food without the wait, they have a to-go counter which is awesome - take your dim sum and sit near the ferry building to enjoy the awesome bay views while you enjoy some tasty dim sum!

As far as Dim Sum goes--it is very tasty and quick and the service is good.  There were a lot of "new" items on the dim sum carts that you wouln't find in a traditional Chinatown dim sum place (like veggie dumplings in a spinach wonton skin)--but I don't mind a little innovation when it comes to old traditions--as long as what's old is still there.  Good dim sum;

My only objection is the price.  I have NEVER paid so much for dim sum in my life!!  I am from LA and was in SF for vacation.  I go to a GREAT dim sum place in Chinatown in LA and leave stuffed for $20.  My girlfriend (not a heavy eater) and I somehow spent $90 at this place?!?!?!!?  For dim sum!!?!?!?  There are no prices ANYWHERE in the menu or on your running tab.  The prices are actually what prompted me to start reviewing (this is my first review)!!!!

It is delicious--but mind your pocketbook.
